#Linux Lab 1 - File System Basics

## Objective
Learn how to navigate the Linux file system

## Commands Practiced
-ls
-mkdir
-rm
-mv
-cp
-vi
-touch
-cd
-cd ..
-pwd
-ls -l
-ls -la
-cat
-mkdir -p

## Example
```bash

# Create/Remove a directory
ls
mkdir documents
mkdir notes pictures games
rmdir games
ls

# Create/Rename a file
touch paper.txt
touch contact.txt phone.txt grades.txt
mv grades.txt color.txt
ls

# Edit file and copy content to another file then delete
vi color.txt
cp color.txt contact.txt
cat color.txt
cat contact.txt
rm color.txt
ls

# Show present directory, Change directory, view list, long list with hidden files
pwd
cd notes
cd ..
ls
ls -l
ls -la

# Created a nested directory & file
mkdir -p color/red
cd color
ls
touch notepad/homework
ls
  148  cd ..
  149  touch notepad/homework
